

download the iso image 

burn an iso image to cd-rom (right click on .iso file, select burn a file to disk) 
OR
build a virtual machine under KVM 
   KVM - bios - set allow virtual machines , edit config file to point to network card 

   add a virtual machine - just follow the instructions

10 things to do after you install freebsd

https://www.tecmint.com/things-to-do-after-installing-freebsd/


The first thing every system administrator should perform after a fresh installation of an operating system is to make sure the system is up-to-date with the latest security patches and the latest versions of the kernel, package manager and software packages. 

freebsd-update fetch
freebsd-update install 

To update “Ports” package manager and installed software run the below command.

# pkg update
# pkg upgrade











